snippet.title: ENHYPEN Talks ‘ROMANCE:UNTOLD,’ Entering Their Romance Era, Working With JVKE | Billboard News
snippet.description:
ENHYPEN has officially entered their romance era with their newest album, ‘ROMANCE:UNTOLD,’ out today. The boys share what it was like to transition from a “darker” sound to a softer one, their favorite tracks off of the album, working with JVKE and more!

3:20: The Boys Share Their Favorite Songs Off Their New Album

snippet.description:
안녕하세요! 오랜만에 나타난 준호입니다!
이번에는 은우와 함께 레트로 감성 넘쳐흐르는 캠코더를 들고 여행을 떠났습니다!🩵

롯데웰푸드와 의성군이 함께하는 의성마늘햄 가족캠프 ‘햄핑’에서
🧄마늘🧄 수확체험도 하고 맛있는 의성마늘햄 순한 시리즈도 먹어보고~ 진짜 배부르고 재밌게 놀고 왔는데요!

snippet.title: The Blacklist | Elizabeth vs The Stewmaker (James Spader)
snippet.description:
After being kidnapped, Elizabeth (Megan Boone) is turned over to The Stewmaker to be disposed of. Meanwhile, Red Reddington (James Spader) try to find her before it's too late.

Watch Season 1-8 on Netflix: https://www.netflix.com/title/70281312
Season 1, Episode 4: "The Stewmaker"

In the two years following the death of Elizabeth Keen, Raymond Reddington (James Spader) and the members of the FBI Task Force have disbanded – their lives now changed in unexpected ways and with Reddington’s whereabouts unknown. Finding themselves each at a crossroads, a common purpose compels them to renew their original mission: to take down dangerous, vicious and eccentric Blacklisters. In the process, they begin to uncover lethal adversaries, unimaginable conspiracies, and surprising betrayals that will threaten alliances and spur vengeance for the past, led by the most devious criminal of them all – Raymond Reddington.

After assassins fool the FBI and invade their black site, Red (James Spader) is forced to drag Agent Ressler (Diego Klattenhoff) away from danger.

Watch Seasons 1-8 on Netflix: https://www.netflix.com/title/70281312
Season 1, Episode 9 "Anslo Garrick"

In the two years following the death of Elizabeth Keen, Raymond Reddington (James Spader) and the members of the FBI Task Force have disbanded – their lives now changed in unexpected ways and with Reddington’s whereabouts unknown. Finding themselves each at a crossroads, a common purpose compels them to renew their original mission: to take down dangerous, vicious and eccentric Blacklisters. In the process, they begin to uncover lethal adversaries, unimaginable conspiracies, and surprising betrayals that will threaten alliances and spur vengeance for the past, led by the most devious criminal of them all – Raymond Reddington.

About The Blacklist: For decades, ex-government agent Raymond “Red” Reddington (James Spader, TV’s “The Office,” “Boston Legal”) has been one of the FBI’s most wanted fugitives. Brokering shadowy deals for criminals across the globe, Red was known by many as “The concierge of Crime.” Now, he’s mysteriously surrendered to the FBI with an explosive offer: he will help catch the world’s most elusive criminals, under the condition that he speaks only to Elizabeth “Liz” Keen (Megan Boone, TV’s “Law & Order: Los Angeles”), an FBI profiler fresh out of Quantico. For Liz, it’s going to be one hell of a first day on the job.

snippet.title: Alec Baldwin Judge Slams Prosecutor For Cutting Her Off: ‘I’m Not Finished’
snippet.description:
Things became fiery in the courtroom on Friday morning during the Alec Baldwin trial as the defense and the state argued over conduct in the courtroom and other issues. When the state cut off the judge and asked to respond to the defense's statement, Judge Sommer responded by saying, "I'm not finished!" When state attorney Kari Morrisey tried to continue talking, Sommer cut her off, hinting to Morrissey to end her statement.

Subscribe to Law&Crime Trials for More Courtroom Coverage: https://bit.ly/LawAndCrimeTrials

Watch More Alec Baldwin Trial Clips: https://bit.ly/AlecBaldwinTrial

Famed actor and movie producer Alec Baldwin was indicted on one count of involuntary manslaughter in January for the death of 42-year-old cinematographer Halyna Hutchins. Hutchins died on Baldwin’s “Rust” movie set. Armorer Hannah Gutierrez-Reed was found guilty of involuntary manslaughter for Hutchins’ death. She was sentenced to 18 months in prison.

snippet.title: Alec Baldwin Attorney Drops Bombshell While Grilling Crime Scene Technician
snippet.description:
While cross-examining a crime scene technician, Alec Baldwin's defense attorney, Alex Spiro, dropped a bombshell saying that a retired officer went to the police station and dropped off live ammunition that killed cinematographer Halyna Hutchins after convicted armorer Hannah Gutierrez-Reed's trial. The officer is reportedly a close friend of the armorer's father. The prosecutor refuted the claim under redirect, stating the ammo brought into the station doesn't match the live ammo on the set of "Rust."

snippet.title: Alec Baldwin’s Lawyers Get Fired Up, Says There’s Too Many Issues in “Rust” Trial
snippet.description:
On the third day of trial, both defense attorneys for defendant Alec Baldwin, Alex Spiro and Luke Nikas, reveal they believe this case has had too many issues. Spiro said, “I’ve been on many high-pressure cases, and there have been more issues in this case than I’ve had throughout my career.” Spiro also said he believes that state attorney Kari Morrisey has been signaling to witnesses on the stand. Nikas got furious regarding the conduct of the prosecution.

localized.title: Alec Baldwin’s Lawyers Get Fired Up, Says There’s Too Many Issues in “Rust” Trial
localized.description:
On the third day of trial, both defense attorneys for defendant Alec Baldwin, Alex Spiro and Luke Nikas, reveal they believe this case has had too many issues. Spiro said, “I’ve been on many high-pressure cases, and there have been more issues in this case than I’ve had throughout my career.” Spiro also said he believes that state attorney Kari Morrisey has been signaling to witnesses on the stand. Nikas got furious regarding the conduct of the prosecution.
